The paper presents a platform for collecting data on ethical decision-making in autonomous vehicles, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the platform is based on the CARLA simulator, which is a robotics simulator, making cs.RO a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of deep reinforcement learning agents, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the platform is designed for the training and tuning of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
